**Anything else relevant?**
I tested some patterns that don't produce this error.
Those lines are working:
```scss
@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto:wght@400;500&display=swap');
@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto:wght@500;700&display=swap');
```

I think this error is produced when there are more then 2 weight-numbers separated by a semicolon.

Update:
This import line here
```scss
@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto+Mono:wght@500;700&family=Roboto:wght@400;500&display=swap');
```
produces this url
```
https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto+Mono:wght@500;700&family=Roboto[_ngcontent-muh-c11]:wght@400;500&display=swap
```
so this time the insert happens on a different place.

### Problem scenario

The issue is in my custom-created module, I imported a component and that component uses a service, then I **ng serve** that component not rendering and give a warning in the console as **Can't bind to 'ngIf' since it isn't a known property of 'ng-container'** and if I remove that service from that component it renders and works fine..but if I add that service into the component it does not render and doesn't show....but I already use that service in other components and it works fine.


